  "prompt": "Why did Thor's hammer shake in the movie \u2018Avengers: Age of Ultron\u2019 when Captain America tried to lift it?",
  "response": "In *Avengers: Age of Ultron*, Thor's hammer, Mjolnir, shakes slightly when Captain America tries to lift it. This moment sparked much discussion among fans, as it subtly hints at Captain America's worthiness.\n\nAccording to the lore of *Thor*, Mjolnir can only be wielded by someone who is \"worthy.\" While Captain America couldn't fully lift the hammer, the slight movement suggests that he is *almost* worthy, or on the brink of being so. This subtle detail foreshadows a later moment in *Avengers: Endgame*, where Captain America proves his worthiness by fully wielding Mjolnir to fight Thanos.\n\nThe scene in *Age of Ultron* serves as a nod to Captain America's character\u2014his integrity, selflessness, and heroism\u2014without fully revealing his worthiness at that time. It\u2019s a clever and layered moment that adds depth to the story and his character arc.",
